[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: 4. Radio Telemetry (APUS)

[GRAMMAR]
ELEMENTS:
- TAG: REQUIREMENT
  FIELDS:
  - TITLE: UID
    TYPE: String
    REQUIRED: True
  - TITLE: STATUS
    TYPE: SingleChoice(Draft, Active, Deprecated)
    REQUIRED: True
  - TITLE: TAGS
    TYPE: Tag
    REQUIRED: False
  - TITLE: STATEMENT
    TYPE: String
    REQUIRED: True
  - TITLE: VERIFICATION
    TYPE: SingleChoice(Test, Inspection, Analysis, Review)
    REQUIRED: False
  - TITLE: RATIONALE
    TYPE: String
    REQUIRED: False
  - TITLE: REFS
    TYPE: String
    REQUIRED: False

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-3000
STATUS: Active
TAGS: Radio, APUS, Physical
STATEMENT: The firmware shall communicate over a DX-LR03-433T30D LoRa module at 433.125 MHz (LORA_FREQ_MHZ), 20 dBm TX power (LORA_TX_POWER), via UART2 at 9600 baud. The physical channel configuration shall be loaded from the active radio config at boot and persisted in flash.
VERIFICATION: Inspection
RATIONALE: APUS-1 / config.h. Physical link parameters are fixed for the current hardware revision. 433 MHz band provides adequate range for typical amateur rocket altitudes (< 3 km).
REFS: docs/standards/apus_standard.md APUS-1, src/config.h LORA_FREQ_MHZ, LORA_TX_POWER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-3001
STATUS: Active
TAGS: Radio, APUS, Framing
STATEMENT: Every transmitted ARES Radio Protocol frame shall begin with the 4-byte sync word 0xAE 0x55 0xC3 0x1A. A receiver shall only begin frame parsing after detecting this exact sync sequence. Frames not preceded by the sync word shall be silently discarded.
VERIFICATION: Test
RATIONALE: APUS-2. The sync word provides frame alignment after link startup or mid-frame corruption. The 32-bit sequence was chosen for low probability of false-positive occurrence in arbitrary byte streams.
REFS: docs/standards/apus_standard.md APUS-2, docs/architecture/ares_radio_protocol.md

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-3002
STATUS: Active
TAGS: Radio, APUS, CRC
STATEMENT: Every transmitted frame shall include a CRC-32 field computed over bytes [4 .. 9+LEN] (excluding the sync word). Received frames whose CRC-32 does not match shall be silently discarded at the driver level. No corrupted data shall reach application logic.
VERIFICATION: Test
RATIONALE: APUS-2. The RF channel is noisy; bit-flip protection is mandatory. CRC-32 (Ethernet polynomial) provides a Hamming distance of 4 for frames up to 512 bytes.
REFS: docs/standards/apus_standard.md APUS-2, docs/architecture/ares_radio_protocol.md

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-3003
STATUS: Active
TAGS: Radio, APUS, Priority
STATEMENT: The radio dispatcher shall schedule frame transmission in priority order: EVENT (PUS ST[5]) > HK report (PUS ST[3]) > LOG. Within the same priority class, scheduling shall be round-robin across pending slots. A single dispatching cycle shall transmit at most one frame.
VERIFICATION: Inspection
RATIONALE: APUS-19. Safety-critical events (anomaly detection, state transitions) must not be starved by high-rate housekeeping telemetry.
REFS: docs/standards/apus_standard.md APUS-19

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-3004
STATUS: Active
TAGS: Radio, APUS, Payload
STATEMENT: A single ARES Radio Protocol frame payload shall not exceed 255 bytes. The HK telemetry payload shall be a fixed 78-byte struct (APUS-3.6), verified at compile time by a static_assert. Scripts that would produce an oversized HK payload due to too many fields shall be rejected at parse time with a descriptive error.
VERIFICATION: Test
RATIONALE: APUS-15. The LoRa module MTU and protocol LEN field (1 byte) limit payload to 255 bytes. Oversized frames would be silently truncated by the driver, corrupting the HK struct alignment. The 78-byte size is enforced by static_assert(sizeof(TelemetryPayload) == 78) in ares_radio_protocol.h.
REFS: docs/standards/apus_standard.md APUS-15, APUS-3.6, src/comms/ares_radio_protocol.h TelemetryPayload

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SRS-3005
STATUS: Active
TAGS: Radio, APUS, NodeID
STATEMENT: The transmitting node ID field in each frame shall be an unsigned byte in the range NODE_ID_MIN (1) to NODE_ID_MAX (253). Node ID 0 is reserved for broadcast; node IDs 254–255 are reserved for ground station addresses. The firmware's own node ID shall be configurable via PUT /api/config and persisted in flash.
VERIFICATION: Test
RATIONALE: APUS-10. Fixed node ID assignments prevent frame collision when multiple ARES units operate in the same RF band during a launch event.
REFS: docs/standards/apus_standard.md APUS-10, src/config.h NODE_ID_MIN, NODE_ID_MAX

